<h1>Newsletters</h1>
	<h2>Creating a newsletter</h2>
	<p>Newsletters are created by the editorial team within their email clients or webmail accounts. As with any email the content can be composed in either rich text, including html or plain text. The CMS may be used to create the html but it ought to be noted that the html will then need to be edited to remove any dynamic content (for example Twitter feeds).</p> 
	<p>Once the team is happy with the email look and content it must be emailed to the specified newsletter address. This can be any TC owned email address and the 'from' address can be different if wished.</p>
	<p>The completed newsletter will be distributed via email therefore the usual recommendations are applicable.</p> 
	<ul>
		<li>It is inadvisable to use large images as some users' email clients may reject larger emails.</li> 
		<li>Subject lines should be chosen carefully to avoid looking like spam.</li> 
		<li>Dynamic content should be avoided.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>Once the newsletter email is sent to the distribution address it will feed into the system.</p>
	<h3 style="color:red">IMPORTANT</h3>
	<p>You must put the word <b>newsletter</b> in the subject line followed by a colon and a space, then enter the subject line you want to appear.</p>
